{"lemma":"ضالّ","slug":"ضالّ","root":"ض.ل.ل","root_slug":"ض-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضالّ","root":"ضلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":14},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25939","n26249"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"straying; roaming; astray; lost"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/dˤaːll/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25939","headword_ar":"ضَالٌّ","root":"Dl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Erring, straying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going astray; deviating from the right way"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from that which is right; missing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"losing, the right way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"losing his way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaluwlN","text_ar":"ضَلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. therewith; (K;) [or rather with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dil~iylN","text_ar":"ضِلِّيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to a general rule:] pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dul~aAlN","text_ar":"ضُلَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [of which see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risolN","text_ar":"رِسْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuAl~uwna","text_ar":"ضُالُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [in the Kur i. last verse,] some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA A@lD~aA^al~iyna","text_ar":"وَلَا ا@لضَّاَلِّينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to avoid the concurrence of two quiescent letters. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAl~N","text_ar":"ضَالٌّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAl~N","text_ar":"تَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O;) in which the latter epithet is an imitative sequent. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tl","text_ar":"تل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Becoming lost;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Forgetting."},{"kind":"text","text":"It is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^anaA mina A@lD~aAl~iyna","text_ar":"وَاَنَا مِنَ ا@لضَّالِّينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur xxvi. 19] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I being of those that forgot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimraA^apN DaAl~apN","text_ar":"اِمرَاَةٌ ضَالَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman forgetting the days of her menstruation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26249","headword_ar":"ضَالٌ","root":"Dyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species of lote-tree called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as are watered only by the rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mountains, which is thinner in its wood than that of the rivers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AHn says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it grows in the plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, tracts, and in the rugged; and the bow that is made of it, when it is pared, is pared so as to be thick, in order that it may be stronger, because of the lightness of its wood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, O, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuboriY~N","text_ar":"عُبْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumoriY~N","text_ar":"عُمْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Another species of tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) AHn says, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tree of the shrub-kind, found in the borders of El-Yemen, rising to the height of a cubit, in its manner of growth like the cypress, and having a yellow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the sort called a"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baramap","text_ar":"بَرَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a very pungent odour, so that its odour comes to you before you reach it: it is not of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thus called."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","M"]}]}}